  <li><strong>Decode the DOCG vs DOC Quality Hierarchy</strong> - Prosecco di Conegliano e Valdobbiadene DOCG represents the pinnacle, with steeper vineyards producing more concentrated flavors and finer bubbles than standard DOC Prosecco. DOCG bottles show more mineral complexity from the hillside soils, while DOC versions from flatter terrain offer fruit-forward profiles at lower prices. Always check for the distinctive neck label that distinguishes DOCG quality.</li>

