  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Prosecco DOCG and DOC classifications?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">DOCG (Denominazione di Origine Controllata e Garantita) represents the highest quality tier, including Conegliano Valdobbiadene and Asolo Prosecco, which must be hand-harvested and undergo stricter production controls. DOC Prosecco covers a broader region with less stringent requirements, resulting in more affordable options that still maintain quality standards. DOCG Proseccos typically offer more complexity, minerality, and aging potential compared to their DOC counterparts.</p>
