    <p class="text-gray-700">Contrary to their names, Extra Dry Prosecco (12-17 g/L residual sugar) is actually sweeter than Brut (0-12 g/L), while Dry Prosecco (17-32 g/L) is the sweetest of the three. Brut offers crisp, clean flavors ideal for aperitifs, Extra Dry provides balanced fruit-forward character perfect for food pairing, and Dry works well with spicy cuisines or as a dessert wine. Most premium producers focus on Brut styles to showcase terroir and winemaking precision.</p>
  </div>

