    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the biggest mistake people make when selecting Prosecco?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">The most common error is choosing based solely on price without considering the occasion—buying expensive DOCG for casual mixing or selecting basic DOC for important celebrations where quality matters. Many consumers also ignore vintage dates, not realizing that Prosecco should be consumed within 2-3 years of release for optimal freshness and fruit character. Understanding sweetness levels is crucial too, as many people mistakenly choose "Dry" expecting a crisp wine when they actually want "Brut."</p>
