  </div>

  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">How do I identify high-quality Prosecco from grocery store options?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Look for DOCG designations (Conegliano Valdobbiadene or Asolo), vintage dates within the last 2 years, and producer names like Bisol, Nino Franco, or Adami for consistent quality. Check the label for "Rive" designations indicating single-commune wines, or "Superiore" for premium selections with stricter production standards. Avoid bottles with generic "Prosecco" labels lacking specific geographic origin, and examine the bottle for fine, persistent bubbles when poured—coarse bubbles often indicate lower quality production.</p>
